<item>
            <title>[SPARK-13929] Use Scala reflection for UDFs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-13929</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ScalaReflection&lt;/tt&gt; uses native Java reflection for User Defined Types which would fail if such types are not plain Scala classes that map 1:1 to Java.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Consider the following extract (from here &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/92024797a4fad594b5314f3f3be5c6be2434de8a/sql/catalyst/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/catalyst/ScalaReflection.scala#L376&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/92024797a4fad594b5314f3f3be5c6be2434de8a/sql/catalyst/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/catalyst/ScalaReflection.scala#L376&lt;/a&gt; ):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; t &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; Utils.classIsLoadable(className) &amp;amp;&amp;amp;
Utils.classForName(className).isAnnotationPresent(classOf[SQLUserDefinedType]) =&amp;gt;

val udt = Utils.classForName(className).getAnnotation(classOf[SQLUserDefinedType]).udt().newInstance()
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//...&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If &lt;tt&gt;t&lt;/tt&gt;&apos;s runtime class is actually synthetic (something that doesn&apos;t exist in Java and hence uses a dollar sign internally), such as nested classes or package objects, the above code will fail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently there are no known use-cases of synthetic user-defined types (hence the minor priority), however it would be best practice to remove plain Java reflection and rely on Scala reflection instead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
